-- Baker Botts Names Corporate Lawyer Baker as Managing Partner
-- B y   I a n   T h o m a s
-- 2012-02-07T23:13:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/baker-botts-names-corporate-lawyer-baker-as-managing-partner.html
Baker Botts LLP , the 725-attorney
international  law firm , named Andrew M. Baker, a corporate
lawyer with 33 years at the firm, as its new managing partner.  Baker’s appointment will take effect April 1, the firm said
today in a statement. He succeeds Walter J. Smith, who will
retire at the end of this year, the Houston-based firm said.  “I am honored that my partners have placed their
confidence in me to continue building on Baker Botts’ reputation
as a ‘best in class’ law firm representing clients globally in
complex matters,” Baker, 56, said in the statement.  Baker, who has offices in Houston and Dallas, joined the
firm in 1979. He currently serves on  Baker Botts ’s executive
committee, and will remain in Houston once he assumes his new
position.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Thomas in New York at 
